      <section eId="sec_9_12_6">
        <num>9-12-6</num>
        <content>
          <p>A verdict may be so amended as to make it conform to the pleadings if the error plainly appears upon the face of the record.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 3421; Code 1868, § 3441; Code 1873, § 3491; Code 1882, § 3491; Civil Code 1895, § 5110; Civil Code 1910, § 5694; Code 1933, § 110-110.)</p>
